12.8 Intro to Executor Service

* Executor Service kya krti h user ko maan lo 5 thread ki jarurat h to executor service
  threadpool me 5 thread ka pool bna diya aur unko start krke rkh liya apne pas aur kahega
  aap kaam dete jayeye me 5cho thread me equally deta rahunga

* Sare task ko queue me arrange kr lega aur jb tk rkhega jb tk puri executor service
  ko nhi maar dete

* jaise hi koi thread khali hua to queue me se 1 task khali thread ko de dega

* thread ko bnane ka aur usse wapas marne ka kaam ab wo nhi krna pad rha h

1. Purpose: ExecutorService is a framework provided by the Java Concurrency API
            to manage and execute submitted tasks without the need to manually manage
            thread life cycles.
2. Thread Pool Management: ExecutorService efficiently reuses a fixed pool of threads
                           to execute tasks, thereby improving performance by reducing
                           the overhead of thread creation, especially for
                           short-lived asynchronous tasks.